Instructions
- Tailwind v4 `@theme {}` replaces `tailwind.config.js` theme extensions. Custom CSS properties defined inside `@theme {}` become Tailwind utility classes automatically (e.g., `--color-sidebar` â†’ `bg-sidebar`, `text-sidebar`).
- The `@import 'tailwindcss'` directive must be the first non-comment line.
- Use CSS custom property naming convention `--color-*` for colors, `--spacing-*` for spacing.
- `@layer base` resets apply to the entire document; keep them minimal.
- The editor uses a dark theme throughout â€” all background tokens should be dark slate shades.
- Status badge pulse animation: define `@keyframes pulse-badge { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.5; } }` and a `.animate-stage-running` utility class.
- Scrollbar styles use `::-webkit-scrollbar`, `::-webkit-scrollbar-track`, `::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb` pseudo-elements.

Deliverable
- `app/globals.css` â€” Tailwind v4 CSS-first global stylesheet with custom design tokens.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (beta or stable) is installed.
- The `@tailwindcss/vite` or `@tailwindcss/postcss` plugin is configured in the build toolchain.
- All components use Tailwind utility classes; no CSS modules are used in this project.

